name: Cabell Tice
bio: All things to @sophieandcrew. Coffee at @drinkdevelop / @orchardcoffee / @cabellcoffee. Fishing, family, outdoors. Waynesville, NC.

social_posts.post_text: Cozy corner in the cafe.
Throwback to summertime.
October’s Fall in NC. All this winter makes me sleepy.

When @sophieandcrew and I found out we were having a baby, we were just kids ourselves. In a little over a month, and at 32, we’re going to see our little Olive turn 9. Can you believe we made this thing?! Love you, Soph. Not a day would be worth it without you.
Snow on the mountain.
Soph and I are bck in Astoria for the weekend. 🏘️ It feels strange to be away on a trip without our 3 littles, but refreshing to be alone together in somewhere familiar yet fresh and new.
The most beautiful thing I’ve ever seen. (Recaption: “no, you posted it..? No…”) Every day gets better with you.
Water color.
A real treat to hear/share songs and a good meal with @israelnebeker, @fawndeviney and @sophieandcrew last night.
Thank you for being so good to us, Astoria. We have many friends we didn’t get to see on this trip, but hopefully we will be back again soon. 🌧️
Catch and release in the Smoky Mountains.
One of my favorite guitars. 1995 D18S. Five years younger than me.
1959 Gibson ES125T my friend @price.stevens found for me this past summer.
Some short clips from our visit to Astoria.
2013 Martin 000-28. Something about this guitar feels special. It’s plays almost like a vintage piece, but it’s still new to the world.
2003 American Standard Telecaster. I’ve had this guitar for about 14 years, but I think it’s time to let it go. Spends far too much time in a case.
Ive been a Molly Parden fan for a while. Last night was a sweet evening hearing her sing songs in our little cafe. Thank you for visiting us in Waynesville, @mollyparden 🙌🏼
Pardon the messy coffee corner. @ryan_dobrowski’s Bent Tree just arrived, and it’s a memory.

I’ve been sorting through negatives that were processed at 39 Depot St when it was Sherrill Studio (1908-1982). Thanks to @wcudigitalcollections I have scans of a few select images that I’ll be printing for @orchardcoffee. This photo must have been taken right when the @blueridgenps opened. How neat to see it covered in snow, much like it has been all week.
My kids are homeschooled and I have a huge crush on the teacher.
Almost 5 years at blue belt and today I moved to purple. Many thanks to my professors and teammates for the training and instruction. @armando_basulto @gracie_waynesville_nc
Started the day working with @theswagnc crew, checking in on their coffee and it was 👌🏽Morning views on top of the mountain are undefeated.
I was taking a photo of Olive and my niece Ines and a customer asked to shoot this one of me taking that photo. It’s rare that I wind up in the pictures, so I’m pretty happy to have this one.
I caught my personal best rainbow trout today. Soph and the kids were there beside me and I wouldn’t have it any other way. Such a fish!
Everybody took turns catching, netting and unhooking. Even @sophieandcrew got on her first fish today. Im so thankful we live somewhere with activities like this just 25 minutes from our door 🪴

My buddy @shuga_____shane is a food wiz and the fare at @breadheadsfoodtruckin is worth the drive! Today he’s in Cherokee at @angryelkbrewing until 7pm. Follow his truck for good eats! @breadheadsfoodtruckin
Where did these two grown boys come from? Can we stop time for just a minute or two.
Afternoon fishing with @shuga_____shane.

Almost doesn’t seem possible, but The Lumineers get better every time. Thanks, @bootjacobson and @brandonmiller128 for being so sweet to me from up on the cat walk. Y’all crushed it at @shakykneesfest 🎉
Little wilds are good fish.
Went to my first ever @ufc fight tonight. What an event the team over there puts on. Pretty wild seats too. Thanks for letting me be your plus 1, @tyler_cain11 🙌🏽
Some wilds I caught while camping in the Great Smoky Mountains.
Been tucking my face behind this camera for a few months and I’ve never had so much fun taking photos 📷
The best cabin experience. Thanks, @theswagnc for your hospitality! 🪴
I made a reel with words. Something I don’t do. On @cabellcoffee soon. This short clip featuring my favorite @chrisstaplesmusic song, and @methodicalcoffee 🪴
Art guy.
A close up look at the garden critters at @theswagnc. Been up here all day with @underground_mountain for an equipment install. Not a bad time or place, and some darn good company.
The teeny tiny world of these little critters is fascinating. Up close with a wide macro gets you right in the thick of it. @theswagnc
One of my favorite trips of the whole year. The 2nd annual Tice, Heinkel, Webster visit to the valley 🪴
I hooked into a pretty little brown trout this evening. Theo got to fight it, Josiah got to net it, and Olive took the hook out. Team work!
I didn’t know what to expect, but Paris blew me away. I now understand how “I went to Paris” can become a personality trait.
August 26, 2013. The best day of my whole life ❤️ 10 years down, a million more. Love you, Soph.
A tune in the airport.
Yellowstone in the summer.
My lil fellas.
Morning 1 back in Europe.
Germany, you were a great 10 days.
Lunch break today in Milan.
The best way to end a work trip is with a vacation week right? Last time we were in Europe together was 12 years ago. It’s going to be a good one.
Duomo Di Como, 2023.
The painting looks as though it’s coming off of the wall.
Florence Day 1.
Last day in Florence. Milan tomorrow, back to the USA on Tuesday.
Back in the US, but more from Italy 🌏
Many of you replied such nice things to Olive’s leaf art in my stories. This is an original idea for her, and I can’t believe her amazing little mind.
Glad it’s still Fall out here in the mountains of western North Carolina.
Still moments from San Francisco.
Shades of LA.
Snaps from @doublechickenpleasenyc from a few weeks back.
He’s a big guy now.
Selects from the Sherrill’s Studio negatives that will be going up on the @orchardcoffee walls soon. Such gems. Thank you @wcudigitalcollections for helping me bring these negatives to life.
Early Christmas with the Bama fam last week was just right 🌲
My favorite little memories of 2023 🪴
Quick zip in and out of NYC.
